<h1>Interactive Game Audio Implementation</h1>

<p class="meta">
FMOD Studio • Adaptive Music • Interactive Audio Systems
</p>

<p>
Designed and implemented a complete interactive audio system for a conceptual top-down action game using FMOD Studio. The project focuses on adaptive music, dynamic ambience, and parameter-driven audio behaviour.
</p>

<p>
The work received a final grade of <strong>83%</strong> and strong academic feedback for both technical implementation and creative sound design.
</p>

<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>
This project explores how interactive audio systems can respond dynamically to gameplay conditions, creating a more immersive and reactive player experience.
</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>

<ul>
<li>Adaptive music driven by gameplay parameters</li>
<li>Health-based intensity changes in real time</li>
<li>Enemy-density driven musical variation</li>
<li>Dynamic environmental ambience system</li>
<li>Randomised environmental audio events (traffic, sirens, wind)</li>
<li>Location-based audio transitions with filtering</li>
<li>Non-linear event structure using FMOD Studio</li>
</ul>

<h2>Tools Used</h2>

<ul>
<li>FMOD Studio</li>
<li>Ableton Live</li>
<li>Custom designed sound assets</li>
</ul>

